main event: A man in Los Angeles, California reported sighting an unidentified flying object in March 1966.
interesting points: The object had a blunt nose, a square pod behind it, and a dome on top and bottom.
The object appeared slightly elongated compared to the size of the moon in the photograph.
The observer could not look directly at the object until the negatives were developed.
The object was photographed using a camera with a 2000mm lens.
The Air Force requested the original negatives to evaluate the sighting.
sighted object: a blunt-nosed, square-shaped object with domes on top and bottom
witnesses: Mr. Maynard J. Weber, a resident of the Copper Brite Cleaners
photographs: yes, photographs were taken but not included in the report
